Shift customer contact to the web, reduce cost and save your users time. FixMyStreet is for local authorities and FixMyTransport is for transport operators.
Our democracy tools include platforms for FoI management and e-Petitions. We also offer an API with up to date data on political representatives’ activities.
Our collaborative action software, PledgeBank,enables people to self-organise effectively and get things together, be it on their street or on a global scale.
Barnet Council was among the first to adopt our popular FixMyStreet software on its website. Barnet’s residents can now easily and quickly to report issues on theirs streets and get them fixed.
Surrey County Council is one of over 30 UK councils using our best in breed e-petitions software. Its great usability means that residents find it easy to submit new petitions or sign existing ones.
We are currently working with Brighton and Hove City Council’s to develop a new, efficeint and user-friendly, web application for managing and publishing Freedom of Information requests..

When Channel 4 launched their key campaigning TV show of 2011, mySociety was called in to deliver the online activism component. We built a platform that gathered signatures and sent them the appropriate parts of government, and a web and mobile app for reporting suspected empty homes to local councils.

mySociety is helping the World Bank to bring street fault reporting technologies to a wider world. Re-using our well known FixMyStreet technology, mySociety is building tools customised to cope with the social, economic and technological environments in these countries.

We built and ran the Number 10 petitions website from 2006-2010, before Parliament took over the responsibility for petitions, which saw 12 million signatures. This tools is now at the heart of our petitions software.
We developed Mapumental – software that visualises public transport travel times, used by property experts, house-hunters, and transport consultants, among others.
MaPit is our web service that maps postcodes and maintains administrative area information for all the United Kingdom.

We have wealth of experience working with complex public transport data sets and geo-mapping. Our FixMyTransport site maps all of the routes and stops, for all public transport modes, in the United Kingdom.
